column1: Alphabet Inc. (GOOGL) is a multinational technology company that specializes in internet-related services and products
column4: and advertising technologies. Here are some key details about the company based on its ticker name:

column1: 1. Founding Details: Google was founded in 1998 by Larry Page and Sergey Brin while they were PhD students at Stanford University. The company started as a research project focused on creating a search engine that used links to rank web pages based on their relevance.
2. Headquarters: Alphabet Inc. is headquartered in Mountain View
3. Products: Google offers a wide range of products and services
4. Revenue Sources: Alphabet Inc.'s main revenue sources come from advertising
column2: which accounts for around 85% of its total revenue. The company also generates revenue through cloud computing

column1: 5. Competitors: Alphabet Inc. faces competition from other technology companies such as Amazon

column2: Alphabet Inc. has a market capitalization of around $1.4 trillion USD.

column1: 7. CEO: The current CEO of Alphabet Inc. is Sundar Pichai.
8. Focus Areas: Alphabet Inc. is focused on developing new technologies and products in areas such as artificial intelligence
column3: and cloud computing. The company is also investing heavily in renewable energy and sustainability initiatives.

column1: 9. Future Plans: Alphabet Inc. plans to continue expanding its product offerings and increasing its presence in emerging markets. The company is also committed to reducing its carbon footprint and promoting sustainability in its operations and supply chain.
